{"TopicId":201400,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Moon rover problem","CreatedByName":"Nin3Foxy","CreatedById":210951,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-01T16:26:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nin3Foxy","CreatedById":210951,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-01T16:26:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI built a lunar rover but near the moon I lose the signal and no longer control the rover.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#32485f;font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EHow do I solve? (the rover is autonomous without people)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Echo__3","CreatedById":204997,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-01T19:14:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat antenna is on the rover and what level is your tracking station? Are you playing with additional\u00A0ground stations?\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/CommNet\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECommNet - Kerbal Space Program Wiki\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-01T19:38:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou ideally need a line of sight as well between your tracking station and rover. Obviously that\u2019s not possible if one or both are facing the other way so you need to set up a network of relay satellites (using relay antennae). It\u2019s a\u00A0bit like using mirrors to angle a laser beam around a corner. As linked above, the wiki gives good info on this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you can\u2019t be bothered with all that, there are\u00A0options\u00A0in the pause menu options to turn off commnet or change what happens if you lose signal etc.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nin3Foxy","CreatedById":210951,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-02T10:29:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947860\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201400\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617304497\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204997\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Echo__3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Echo__3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EQual \u00E8 l\u0027antenna del rover e qual \u00E8 il livello della tua stazione di rilevamento? \u003C/font\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EStai giocando con stazioni di terra aggiuntive?\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/CommNet\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003ECommNet - Wiki del Kerbal Space Program\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f8f9fa;color:#202124;font-size:28px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003Eno, I\u0027m in the sandbox, the antenna I don\u0027t know\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nin3Foxy","CreatedById":210951,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-02T10:29:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947872\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201400\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617305935\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210116\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FruitGoose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, FruitGoose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EIdealmente hai bisogno anche di una linea di vista tra la tua stazione di rilevamento e il rover. \u003C/font\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EOvviamente ci\u00F2 non \u00E8 possibile se uno o entrambi sono rivolti dall\u0027altra parte, quindi \u00E8 necessario creare una rete di satelliti rel\u00E8 (utilizzando antenne rel\u00E8). \u003C/font\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u00C8 un po \u0027come usare degli specchi per inclinare un raggio laser dietro un angolo. \u003C/font\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003ECome collegato sopra, il wiki fornisce buone informazioni su questo. \u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003ESe non puoi essere disturbato da tutto ci\u00F2, ci sono opzioni nelle opzioni del menu di pausa per disattivare la comunicazione o cambiare cosa succede se perdi il segnale, ecc.\u00A0 \u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nokok, i try\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nin3Foxy","CreatedById":210951,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-02T10:29:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}